TITLE: Kharkiv Tried to Return to Normal. Russian Shelling Wouldn’t Let It.
SUMMARY: Ukraine repelled the effort to capture its second-largest city, but the artillery attacks did not stop. Many residents who left have returned but fear that a new offensive is imminent.

SUMMARY: Leaving captured men, women and children in prisons and camps run by Kurds risks seeding a new global terrorism disaster, rights groups and the U.S. military warn.

SUMMARY: Boston’s new police commissioner, Michael Cox, was the victim of an assault by fellow officers who mistook him for a suspect.

TITLE: Hey, Is Anybody Watching the Interns?
SUMMARY: School is out for the summer — but in some cases, so are the bosses.

TITLE: The Burger Recipe J. Kenji Lopez-Alt Can’t Improve (Only Tweak)
SUMMARY: Oklahoma onion burgers, which cook in moments, are so perfect in their simplicity that they can’t be better, he writes.

TITLE: When We Consent, We Shouldn’t Feel Terrible After, Right?
SUMMARY: We deserve more than sex that is merely legal.

TITLE: Climate Politics Are Worse Than You Think
SUMMARY: If only it were just about money.

TITLE: Manchin’s ‘Veto’ of the Climate Bill, as the World Heats Up
SUMMARY: Reaction to Senator Joe Manchin’s rejection of a climate bill. Also: Liz Cheney; sensitive language; erosion of trust in experts; the right to travel.

TITLE: Bodega Clerk Who Fatally Stabbed Man Will Not Face Charges
SUMMARY: Alvin Bragg, Manhattan’s district attorney, said a murder charge against Jose Alba could not be proved. Mr. Alba’s supporters said he acted in self-defense.

TITLE: This Political Neophyte Is a Lock for Congress. His Name Helps.
SUMMARY: Rob Menendez Jr., 37, is running his first race for office for a New Jersey congressional seat that his father, Senator Bob Menendez, once held.

TITLE: How to Keep Your Dog or Cat Cool and Safe During a Heat Wave
SUMMARY: Extreme temperatures pose particular dangers to furry friends.

TITLE: What’s Behind Europe’s Heat Waves?
SUMMARY: This year’s scorching weather is in keeping with a trend. Scientists say a number of factors, including changes in the jet stream, are in play.

TITLE: How ‘Stop the Steal’ Captured the American Right
SUMMARY: The movement to reinstate President Trump has gone far beyond him — and now threatens the future of American elections.

TITLE: Trump National Security Aide Expected to Testify at Jan. 6 Hearing
SUMMARY: Matthew Pottinger, who resigned on the day of the Capitol riot, is expected to be among those at the prime-time session on Thursday, along with Sarah Matthews, a former deputy press secretary.

SUMMARY: The gunman used a rifle to kill three people and injure two others before he was shot dead. He had spent an hour inside a mall bathroom apparently preparing for the attack.

SUMMARY: The sounds of gunfire and children screaming filled the courtroom. Jurors will decide whether the man who killed 17 people in 2018 will be sentenced to death.

SUMMARY: The disappearance of ordinary savers’ money, and the government’s seemingly indifferent response, could pose a major test for the Communist Party’s legitimacy.

SUMMARY: The Republican Party isn’t capable of governing a democracy. And yet Democrats keep helping some of its most unhinged candidates.

TITLE: The Anti-Abortion Movement’s Contempt for Women Is Worse Than I Imagined
SUMMARY: Some Republicans reject even lifesaving abortions.

TITLE: Why Housing Is So Expensive — Particularly in Blue States
SUMMARY: The urban economist Jenny Schuetz breaks down America’s housing crises, the policies that could fix them and the politics standing in the way.

TITLE: One of America’s Most Seductive States Is Also One of Its Scariest
SUMMARY: North Carolina holds an illuminating — and alarming — political mirror up to the country.

TITLE: Joe Manchin Is a Symptom, but It’s the Senate That’s Sick
SUMMARY: It’s no accident that climate legislation has repeatedly been passed in the House only to collapse in the Senate.

TITLE: Election Conspiracy Theories Have Become Central to the Republican Party
SUMMARY: Why election conspiracy theories have become central to the Republican Party.

TITLE: Broken Climate Pledges and Europe’s Heat Wave
SUMMARY: Has the era of global cooperation over planet-warming emissions ended?

TITLE: ‘Son of Elsewhere’ Recounts Life as a Young Immigrant
SUMMARY: Elamin Abdelmahmoud talks about his new memoir, and Sally Denton discusses “The Colony: Faith and Blood in a Promised Land.”

TITLE: Recommended Reading on America’s Authoritarian Enclaves
SUMMARY: Joan Didion’s “Slouching Towards Bethlehem” and Robert Mickey’s “Paths Out of Dixie” help our columnist understand American democracy’s new crisis of authoritarianism.

TITLE: Where Dalí Once Painted the Sea, Wind Turbines Are Set to Rise

TITLE: Colleges Are Resisting Demands to Provide the Abortion Pill
SUMMARY: Even in states that protect abortion rights, colleges are proceeding with caution.

TITLE: What to Look for in a Physical Therapist
SUMMARY: Not all P.T.s are created equal. Find a professional who values evidence over anecdote.

SUMMARY: Foods like yogurt, kimchi, sauerkraut and kombucha increased the diversity of gut microbes and led to lower levels of inflammation.

TITLE: The Unknowability of Other People’s Pain
SUMMARY: While my father was alive, it was impossible for me to imagine his agony.
